PHP Bridge Rules (bridge.php):

Role:
- Acts as middleware between Java tests and PowerDNS PHP library

Responsibilities:
- Accept HTTP requests: bridge.php?action=<method>
- Initialize DN\PowerDNS\API\API
- Execute requested method
- Return JSON response

Design Constraints:
- Keep bridge logic thin (no business logic)
- Delegate all logic to DN\PowerDNS library
- Ensure consistent JSON response structure

Error Handling:
- Catch exceptions and return structured error responses
- Do NOT expose sensitive details (API key)

Logging:
- Ensure all requests pass through RequestLogger
- Include:
  - action
  - payload
  - response
  - timestamps

Validation:
- Validate input parameters before invoking library methods

Do NOT:
- Embed test logic inside PHP
- Duplicate logic already present in library